snippet.textDisplay: "Guess my ethnicity", but most of these guesses were American-centric race labels. Ethnicity is a broader term that relates to ancestry and region, not a social construction that changes based on where you are in the world. Also Muslim isn't an ethnicity, but depending on who you talk to Jewish is. Solid video though since it shows how and why people label each other, just wish that there was a cohesive definition that the guessers were going by for this one.
